#~ msgid "When I start KMyMoney I get a \"Malformed URL\" error. What's wrong?"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Kada pokrenem KMyMoney dobijem grešku \"Deformiran URL\". U čemu je "
#~ "problem?"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Usually the reason for this is that you didn't run 'make install' as "
#~ "root. This step actually copies all of the icons, and other files needed "
#~ "by KMyMoney to run properly. If you did run this, make sure you passed "
#~ "the correct prefix to cmake at the beginning of your compile. See the "
#~ "section on <link linkend=\"installation.fromsource\">compiling from "
#~ "source</link> for more information."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Obično, razlog za ovo je to što niste pokrenuli 'napravi instaliraj' kao "
#~ "root. Ovaj korak, ustvari kopira sve ikone, i druge datoteke koje su "
#~ "potrebne da bi KMyMonez funkcionisao ispravno . Ako ste pokrenuli ovo, "
#~ "osigurajte se da ste proslijedili ispravan prefiks cmake-u na početku "
#~ "vašeg kompajliranja. Pogledajte paragraf na <link linkend=\"installation."
#~ "fromsource\">kompjliranje iz izvora</link> za više informacija."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "When I compile from source, all the icons show up as missing. What did I "
#~ "do wrong?"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Kada kompajliram iz izvora, pojavi se poruka da nema niti jedne ikone. "
#~ "Šta sam uradio/la pogrešno?"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Usually the reason for this is that you didn't run 'make install' as "
#~ "root. See the previous question/answer for more information."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Obično, razlog za ovo je to što niste pokrenuli 'napravi instaliraj' kao "
#~ "root. Pogledajte prethodno pitanje/odgovor za više informacija."

#~ msgid "What options are useful to pass to cmake?"
#~ msgstr "Koje opcije su korisne za proslijeđivanje cmake-u?"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "The most important option is -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX. This specifies where "
#~ "you want to install KMyMoney; it should be the same location where &kde; "
#~ "is installed. In many distributions, cmake will find this location on its "
#~ "own, but if it can't, you can use the command line tool <command>kde4-"
#~ "config --prefix</command> to read out what the prefix should be. For "
#~ "&RedHat;-based distributions, including Mandriva and Fedora, &kde; is "
#~ "installed in <filename role=\"directory\">/usr</filename>."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Najvažnija opcija je -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX. Ovo specificira mjesto gdje "
#~ "želite instalirati KMyMoney;, trebalo bi biti isto kao i lokacija gdje je "
#~ "&kde; instaliran. U više izdanja, cmake će sam pronaći ovu lokaciju, ali "
#~ "ako ne uspije, možete koristiti alat iz komandne linije <command>kde4-"
#~ "config --prefix</command> da pročitate šta bi prefiks trebao biti. Za "
#~ "izdanja bazirana na &RedHat;, kao što su Mandriva i Fedora, &kde; je "
#~ "instaliran u <filename role=\"directory\">/usr</filename>."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Another useful option is -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE. Normally this is not set, "
#~ "but if it is set to Debug, it will allow you to build KMyMoney with debug "
#~ "symbols, which help in trying to figure out crashes. This option is "
#~ "essential if you are a developer and want to contribute."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Još jedna korisna opcija je -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE. Inače, ova opcija nije "
#~ "podešena, ali ako je podešena na Debug, omogućit će vam da pokrenete "
#~ "KMyMoney sa debug simbolima, koji pomažu u pokušajima otkrivanja uzroka "
#~ "krahiranja. Ova opcija je neophodna ako ste razvojni inženjer i želite da "
#~ "doprinesete razvoju."

#~ msgid "The Git version is broken! What do I do now?"
#~ msgstr "Git verzija je oštećena! Šta da uradim sada?"

#, fuzzy
#~| msgid ""
#~| "Usually the reason for this is that one of the developers made a change "
#~| "to the code that requires a clean reconfigure. See the end of the "
#~| "section on <link linkend=\"installation.fromsource\">compiling from "
#~| "source</link> for instructions. If you follow these steps carefully, and "
#~| "still have a problem compiling, please post a message to the &kappname; "
#~| "Developers List at &devlist;, and include the failed output of either "
#~| "the cmake or make command."
